commentText: The best version of Honduras so far.
Perfect Kenya
Kenya which was brewed previously was better. This brew was little bit too short in time. Brew time suppose to be longer than 2:30
Brewing time affect bitterness. Longer brewing time higher bitterness
Nothing special.
Try with coarser grind. This grind was too fine, and extraction time was long.
Coarser grind goes better with with this coffee.
Good Honduras. A lot of flavors extracted.
Medium fine grinding too fine for this coffee. Try with medium or even medium coarse. Not to many flavors extracted
Ratio was too tight. Coffee has a lot of bitterness and intensity, try with higher ratio, and coarser grind.
Clear and strong coffee with a lot of fruity, nutty and choco flavors.
Try with coarser grind.
Good Guatemala.
Grinding wasn't completely good. I think ratio was too tight. Next time try with finer grind and tighter ratio or coarser grind and wider ratio.
Extraction was good. More coffee and more water works well. Next time try with coarser grind
Great coffee, higher ratio works well. Next brew try to keep the ratio but grind coffee one step finer or try one step coarser but try 4:6 pouring.

Balanced bitterness and acidity, medium sweetness. Coffee was good in general. Compared to previous brew with this coffee this time finer grind was tired, but still doesn't show different results compared to previous brew. Next time try coarser grind, two times finer.
Finer grinding adds a lot of bitterness. Coarser grind and wider ratio goes better with this coffee. Next brew remain with the same grind but expand the ratio.

Coffee doesn't expose too many flavors. So far more than 5 different brews was tried and non of them was enough good. It seems that this coffee was roasted too dark and bitter flavors cannot be cover with tried brews.

Very bad coffee was gotten by this brew parameters. Coffee still doesn't expose any extra flavors. Inconsistent grind may affect this bad brew. Both higher acidity and bitterness are singed that coffee is not over or under extracted. Next brew: try even higher ratio and keep the same grind settings
So far the best Costa Rica brew. Next time try medium coarse grind and keep the same all the other parameters.
Balanced coffee. So far the best version of El Salvador. Extraction time under 3 minutes works good. All other brews which are over 3 minutes yields bitter cup of coffee.
Coffee was good, but extremely week. More sweetness was exposed. Fruity and choco flavors
Coffee was overextracted. Ratio was too tight and grinding was too fine, undrinkable.
Very good Slavador!
Coffee wasn't bad. Too bitter. Not to many flavors exposed. Keep the same ratio, but grind coffee more fine.

Well balanced Honduras. 
Try even finer grind, keep the same ratio.

coffee wasn't bad. Unusual flavors exposed (Fruity + Nutty). Grinding wasn't uniform. 
Next time try Coarser grind.
The best version of Honduras so far.
Very good Honduras, grinding works well with this coffee.
Medium fine grinding doesn't work well. Next time try with coarser grind and keep the same ratio.
Tes test test test test test

Freshly roasted coffee. Coffee is good. Cup is balanced without variations in taste. For this brew we used Medium-Medium Coarse grind. With this brewing parameters coffee seems little weak, and underextracted. But, still very good for those who like balanced and not to strong cup. Next brew 1:12 R
Moderate cup of coffee. More coffee with the same grind doesn't work well. Also, grind was uneven. Try to keep ratio 1:17 but grind coffee more finer.

Perfect coffee. Medium coarse grind and 1:16 ratio works well. Coffee isn't that intense. Next brew try finer grind (medium). Keep the same all the other variables.

Very good Columbia. Same ratio was used compared to previous brewing. With this brewing less coffee (13g) and less water (200) was used, also medium grinding. Extraction time was shorter 30-40 sec., and together with medium grind we have  little more intense coffee than previous cup.

Very good cup. With medium fine settings it is managed to lower acidity to minimum, but still good acids can be exposed. Also, bitterness remain low. Both acidity and bitterness are balanced which expose fundamental coffee taste. Not to many flavors pop up from coffee but cup is balanced.
Clean cup. Next brew finer settings.
Moderate cup of coffee. Next brew try to set coarser settings, and use more coffee in order to extend brewing time and enhance more flavors.
